WEBVTT

00:01.088 --> 00:03.177
So, yeah, the first 10 years
of my life,

00:03.220 --> 00:05.135
I called it a "teethbrush,"
but in my defense,

00:05.179 --> 00:07.181
you brush your teeth,
not your tooth!

00:08.225 --> 00:09.270
Hey, you guys even
listening to me?

00:09.313 --> 00:11.489
We most definitely
are not.

00:11.533 --> 00:12.882
Uh, sorry, Miggy.

00:12.925 --> 00:14.318
I realized
I forgot my floss again.

00:14.362 --> 00:15.885
You carry floss aroundwith you?

00:15.928 --> 00:17.321
Like in the containeror loose?

00:17.365 --> 00:18.888
Container, Miggy.

00:18.931 --> 00:20.629
It's for my overnight bag
for Douglas'.

00:20.672 --> 00:21.847
I'm always packing
and repacking it.

00:21.891 --> 00:23.110
Forgetting things.

00:23.153 --> 00:25.895
Spent a whole day
without a bra once.

00:25.938 --> 00:28.245
Felt unhinged.
And a little sexy.

00:28.289 --> 00:30.291
Hey, doesn't Douglas ever
sleep at your house?Never.

00:30.334 --> 00:31.335
My place
is more comfortable.

00:31.379 --> 00:32.989
We're happier there.

00:33.033 --> 00:35.296
Excuse me? I don't remember you
asking me how I felt about it.

00:35.339 --> 00:38.342
My sheets are hand-loomed
in the fjords of Norway.

00:38.386 --> 00:39.952
They only make
two sets a year.

00:39.996 --> 00:41.432
I just thought
it was safe to assume.

00:41.476 --> 00:42.955
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Guys!

00:42.999 --> 00:44.131
Stop fighting!

00:44.174 --> 00:45.436
We're not fighting.

00:45.480 --> 00:46.568
We're just having
a playful back-and-forth.

00:46.611 --> 00:48.222
Okay, I'll fix this.

00:48.265 --> 00:50.485
Douglas, tonight, you have tospend the night at Poppy's.

00:50.528 --> 00:53.357
Don't bother, Miggy.
Douglas is stuck in his ways.

00:53.401 --> 00:55.098
Hey, I take issue
with that.

00:55.142 --> 00:58.319
You know, in 1972,
I camped out for three nights

00:58.362 --> 01:01.148
on a Buffalo sidewalk
just to get Sabre tickets?

01:01.191 --> 01:03.324
We had to huddle together
for warmth.

01:03.367 --> 01:06.327
But with close proximity
comes disease.

01:08.416 --> 01:09.243
Gregory...

01:09.286 --> 01:12.202
Oh, anyway, listen, Poppy,
if you want,

01:12.246 --> 01:13.377
I'll, uh -- I'll spend the nightat your place.

01:13.421 --> 01:14.465
Aww!

01:14.509 --> 01:16.380
Wait, should we talk
about Gregory? 'Cause...

01:16.424 --> 01:17.686
You know what?
Forget it.

01:17.729 --> 01:19.688
Turn your head, Miggy.
I'm gonna kiss this man.

01:19.731 --> 01:20.689
Bring it in.
Mm-hmm.

01:20.732 --> 01:21.690
Mm!
Mwah!
Aww.

01:21.733 --> 01:23.996
Get ready for the best night
of your life.

01:24.040 --> 01:24.997
[ Knock on door ]

01:25.041 --> 01:26.173
Hey.

01:26.216 --> 01:27.304
Damn you.

01:27.348 --> 01:30.220
Last night was the worst nightof my life!

01:30.264 --> 01:32.570
High five, my man.
Nowhere to go but up!

01:33.615 --> 01:36.922
--Captions by VITAC--

01:36.966 --> 01:38.881
Douglas: Gregory.

01:40.274 --> 01:41.579
It smells weird
in here.

01:41.623 --> 01:42.928
It's probably
Graham's lunch.

01:42.972 --> 01:44.016
Yeah,
we only had eggs,

01:44.060 --> 01:45.801
so I boiled six,
called it a day.

01:45.844 --> 01:47.368
Oh, hey, Colin.

01:47.411 --> 01:48.586
Colin:
Oh, hi, Angie.

01:48.630 --> 01:50.153
How's it going?

01:50.197 --> 01:51.154
Oh, you know,

01:51.198 --> 01:53.200
pretty bog-standard day
so far.

01:53.243 --> 01:55.071
Yeah.

01:56.203 --> 01:58.161
That's...good.

01:58.205 --> 02:00.294
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:02.209 --> 02:03.384
Well, uh,
yeah, cheers.

02:03.427 --> 02:05.516
Hee-hee.
Yeah.

02:05.560 --> 02:08.302
What in Cupid's tiny grave
just happened?

02:08.345 --> 02:09.738
I have goose bumps

02:09.781 --> 02:11.392
and obviously not
the good kind.

02:11.435 --> 02:12.219
Things with Colin and me

02:12.262 --> 02:14.221
kind of cooled downsince Valentine's Day.

02:14.264 --> 02:15.396
Really? Why?

02:15.439 --> 02:17.441
I thought you guys shared
some heat on the swing set.

02:17.485 --> 02:19.400
You were all
[Imitates techno beat]

02:19.443 --> 02:20.531
Okay, what did I tell youabout fist pumping? No.

02:20.575 --> 02:22.533
Right.[ Sighs ] And, yeah,we did have heat, alright?

02:22.577 --> 02:23.795
So much thatit was probably inappropriate

02:23.839 --> 02:25.101
on school property.

02:25.145 --> 02:27.538
But nothing
has happened since.
Ohh.

02:27.582 --> 02:30.454
Do you think maybe he just
sees you as a mom from class?

02:30.498 --> 02:32.326
[ Scoffs ]
A mom from class?!

02:32.369 --> 02:33.762
Excuse me?

02:33.805 --> 02:37.548
Uh, sir, I invite youto check out the merchandise.

02:37.592 --> 02:38.593
Not too much.

02:38.636 --> 02:40.464
All I need to do
is get Colin alone,

02:40.508 --> 02:42.292
bust out my A-game,and he'll be powerless.

02:42.336 --> 02:44.076
I just need an in.

02:44.120 --> 02:45.295
Rory: What about Sophie?

02:45.339 --> 02:47.993
I mean, she's desk mates
with Colin's kid.

02:48.037 --> 02:50.387
Percy? I don't know
if Sophie likes him very much.

02:50.431 --> 02:52.346
No one likes him.
Kid's obsessed with apples.

02:52.389 --> 02:55.349
Amy: The way he talks
about Fujis...[ Sighs ]

02:55.392 --> 02:56.393
...is chilling.

02:56.437 --> 02:58.439
God,
I'd kill for a hobby.

02:58.482 --> 02:59.483
Anyway, thanks, kids.

02:59.527 --> 03:01.442
Beat it.

03:01.485 --> 03:02.878
Oh, my God.Will, that is perfect.

03:02.921 --> 03:05.010
I'll just invite Colin overfor a playdate tonight.

03:05.054 --> 03:06.708
Can I borrow your daughter
for bait?

03:06.751 --> 03:09.145
Ho'd up. I thought we
were taking Graham and
Sophie for pizza tonight.

03:09.189 --> 03:11.234
We've been planning this
for awhile.

03:11.278 --> 03:13.497
I have been micro-dosing LACTAIDsince Monday.

03:13.541 --> 03:15.456
Sorry, bro,this is more important.

03:15.499 --> 03:17.284
Here comes
the apple man.

03:18.110 --> 03:20.591
Why would you force me
to sleep at Poppy's?

03:20.635 --> 03:23.028
My whole body is destroyed.
Here, feel this.

03:23.072 --> 03:24.247
It's the L5.

03:24.291 --> 03:26.249
Yikes.That disk wants out.

03:26.293 --> 03:27.642
Yeah, the whole experience
was a nightmare,

03:27.685 --> 03:29.034
from soup to nuts.

03:29.078 --> 03:32.081
First of all, I couldn't have
my usual nightcap

03:32.124 --> 03:34.518
because Poppy doesn't have
any single-malt whiskey,

03:34.562 --> 03:35.911
so I had to drink
red wine

03:35.954 --> 03:38.740
like a maÃ®tre d'
closing up for the night.

03:38.783 --> 03:41.395
Then I'm in her
bathroom, which is the
size of an Alfa Romeo.

03:41.438 --> 03:42.309
Not a reference I get.

03:42.352 --> 03:44.659
It's a small car,
Miggy.
If you say so.

03:44.702 --> 03:45.964
I go to
brush my teeth,

03:46.008 --> 03:47.923
and there's nowhere
to put the brush down

03:47.966 --> 03:50.273
'cause of the hundreds
of candles and trinkets

03:50.317 --> 03:52.754
and just the tops
of somany things.

03:52.797 --> 03:54.886
So I put it
on the back of the toilet

03:54.930 --> 03:56.932
like a gigolo
in a Denny's bathroom.

03:56.975 --> 04:00.457
Then the clock strikes 8:45,
so I gotta make.

04:00.501 --> 04:01.676
Make what?

04:01.719 --> 04:03.417
Make peace
with my dinner.

04:03.460 --> 04:04.461
Still don't get it.

04:04.505 --> 04:05.854
Dookie, Miggy!

04:05.897 --> 04:06.985
Oh.
Drop anchor!

04:07.029 --> 04:09.205
Release the hounds!
Come on!

04:09.249 --> 04:11.338
But the problem is
the toilet is just 6 inches

04:11.381 --> 04:13.427
from her bedroom...[ Laughter on TV]

04:13.470 --> 04:15.298
...separated by a wall
the width of a grape nut.

04:15.342 --> 04:16.908
So the chickens
can't come home to roost,

04:16.952 --> 04:18.083
if you know what I mean.

04:18.127 --> 04:19.346
You know I've never seena chicken in real life?

04:20.738 --> 04:23.175
So, I'm blocked
like a stalled cement truck

04:23.219 --> 04:24.481
and just want to relax,

04:24.525 --> 04:26.570
but Poppy's watching "Frasier,"
full volume.

04:26.614 --> 04:29.747
You know what Roz's voice
sounds like with a subwoofer?

04:29.791 --> 04:32.228
She was laughing
like it's brand-new.

04:32.272 --> 04:34.578
[ Laughs ]Roz, you tell it like it is!

04:34.622 --> 04:36.754
And she keeps it on
while she falls asleep.

04:36.798 --> 04:39.409
But here's the worst part --
the bed!

04:39.453 --> 04:41.368
That mattress
came after me

04:41.411 --> 04:43.326
like I had done something
to its family.

04:43.370 --> 04:44.762
Wow. Some night.

04:44.806 --> 04:47.809
I hate to see a tall,rich white man suffer like that.

04:47.852 --> 04:49.376
So, what are you
gonna do?

04:49.419 --> 04:50.812
I-I don't know
what I'm gonna do,

04:50.855 --> 04:52.204
but I-I can't
say anything,

04:52.248 --> 04:53.945
'cause I don't want
to hurt her feelings.

04:53.989 --> 04:55.338
Hey!

04:55.382 --> 04:56.557
[ Chuckles ]

04:56.600 --> 04:58.123
I thought I heard you
clomping around up here.

04:58.167 --> 04:59.603
Either that,
or Miggy bought a pony.

04:59.647 --> 05:01.823
[ Both laugh ]
Hey.

05:01.866 --> 05:04.913
Anyway, I just wanted to say
last night was amazing,

05:04.956 --> 05:06.480
and it just --

05:06.523 --> 05:08.177
it means so much to me
that you stayed over.

05:08.220 --> 05:09.352
You know,
it's funny --

05:09.396 --> 05:10.962
I was just telling Miggy
how much I loved it.

05:11.006 --> 05:12.964
[ Gasps ] Oh.

05:13.008 --> 05:14.270
Oh, he was!
He was.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.620
I was like, "Did you love it?"And he was like, "Yes."

05:16.664 --> 05:18.970
And I was like, "How much?"And he was like, "A lot."

05:19.014 --> 05:21.495
And I was like, "No, no,quantify it specifically."

05:21.538 --> 05:22.974
And he was like,
"Five stars."

05:23.018 --> 05:25.020
And I was like,"Out of how many stars?"

05:25.063 --> 05:26.238
And then you walked in.

05:26.282 --> 05:27.370
[ Chuckles ]
Aww.

05:27.414 --> 05:29.633
In fact,he wants to do it again.

05:29.677 --> 05:30.852
Really?!

05:30.895 --> 05:32.070
Tonight!

05:32.114 --> 05:33.507
Ohhh!

05:33.550 --> 05:35.073
